text: There is a Dmitry Galkovsky lecture on Spanish culture and art where he's talking about Diego Velazquez and just says "this is a creature with a huge hypertrophied brain that understands everything about life"

On Mayakovsky: "This is the laser of a huge brain groping in the darkness, suddenly establishing contact with the reader's brain and in a few minutes transmitting to it the concentrated power of thoughts, feelings, will, desire to live, irony, laughter, pity, despair and hope."

My grandpa who was a communist used to say similar stuff, said the old communists were idealists but the new ones were corrupt because they didn't care about the people so betrayed the country... Spent his last years voting for the far-right and watching the RW TV channel all day

That last generation of real communists who are now all in their 80s all talk the same way, communism is a state of mind, the new generation lacked the original zeal and patriotism they had, etc. They ACTUALLY believe in communism instead of it just being just an aesthetic thing.
Where was this if not a secret?
